Value: Assure adequate, timely and cost-efficient grid capacity and topology that enables current and future users to connect and flow power safely, reliably, and affordably.
Provide non-discriminatory, timely, and cost-transparent physical connection tailored to the customer's location, capacity, and quality needs, compliant with codes.
Deliver reliable, high-availability power transport and quality within contracted parameters using existing grid assets.
Maintain real-time system balance and security to prevent outages and keep frequency/voltage within limits.
Provide accurate, transparent settlements, charges, and operational data to market participants and regulators.
